The paper deals with the problem of counting the number of inequivalent MBFs, which is a topic in discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The approach proposed involves breaking the calculation into parts based on the profiles of these functions, which suggests a connection to computational complexity (cs.CC) and data structures (cs.DS). The problem also involves combinatorial aspects, which are relevant to the sub-categories of information theory (cs.IT) and logic in computer science (cs.LO).
